.TH "sys_rt_sigsuspend" 9 "sys_rt_sigsuspend" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sys_rt_sigsuspend \- replace the signal mask for a value with the @unewset value until a signal is received
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "long" sys_rt_sigsuspend
.BI "(sigset_t __user * unewset "  ","
.BI "size_t sigsetsize "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "unewset" 12
new signal mask value
.IP "sigsetsize" 12
size of sigset_t type
